			<unit id="122" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>An address book is one example of a data set that can be much easier to navigate using a semantic zoom control.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="123" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>In one view is the complete, alphanumerical overview of people in the address book (left image), while the zoomed-in view displays the data in order and with greater detail (right image).</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="124" translate="yes">
